sbol:ComponentDefinition.addgene:aPortionOfThisPlasmidWasDerivedF: The CROP-sgRNA-MS2 lentiviral backbone was synthesized by VectorBuilder by adapting the CROP-seq vector (Datlinger et al. 2017) with the following modifications: 1) the sgRNA scaffold sequence contains two MS2 loops that allow recruitment of MS2-p65-HSF1 in SAM ESCs; and 2) a fluorescent mCherry marker was included downstream of the EF1α promoter and linked through T2A to a puromycin resistance cassette, allowing assessment of the multiplicity-of-infection (MOI) by FACS and antibiotic selection of the cells
